<TEXT>
gymnich castle which housed former 
president reagan and other government guests will become part of 
an exclusive resort for wellheeled golf enthusiasts under its new 
japanese owner 
developer masao nangaku on thursday unveiled a 72 million 
project to turn the castle grounds into a luxurious complex 
including an 18hole golf course and a hotel for 1250 guests 
the 14thcentury castle has been used in the past as a 
government guest house 
reagan and his wife nancy stayed at gymnich castle about 18 
miles from bonn on their visit to west germany and the western 
economic summit in may 1985 
baron joerg adolf sigismund von holzschuher sold the moated 
rosecolored stone castle to nangaku in 1987 for 15 million the 
castle grounds have belonged to the german aristocratic family 
since the 12th century 
work on the grounds will not begin until reconstruction of the 
main house atop the petersberg hill overlooking the rhine river is 
completed this year 
nangaku heads the minamiholdings gmbh company based in nearby 
duesseldorf he is reputed to be one of japans wealthiest men and 
a major collector of the works of the late spanish artist salvador 
dali 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

