instruction in public schools and to offer foreign languages to 
students as early as the first grade 
the report said each state should come up with its own realistic 
and innovative plan for finding new markets and developing new 
products that will be in demand by foreign nations governors can 
elevate foreign trade to a top priority and increase public 
awareness of the connections between their own economy and 
international markets it said 
we can do something about international competition baliles 
said we can develop an export culture we can develop programs 
that identify markets 
the report suggested governors appoint a trade czar an 
official with state cabinetlevel rank who would direct and 
coordinate the state plan for encouraging international trade 
it said state governments should help firms obtain financing for 
export deals either through direct loans and loanguarantee 
programs or by serving as brokers and clearinghouses to match 
commercial lenders with businesses 
