<TEXT>
two graduate students says they detected 
indications of cold fusion in an experiment they conducted with 
heavy water while georgia tech researchers now are saying their 
own results may have been flawed 
van l eden and wei liu physics students at the university of 
washington said thursday they failed to duplicate exactly the 
highly publicized experiment by university of utah chemist b 
stanley pons and martin fleischmann of englands university of 
southampton but they did get indications fusion may have taken 
place in their experiment last week 
pons and fleischmann said they apparently produced nuclear 
fusion in a tabletop experiment using ordinary lab equipment 
meanwhile georgia tech researchers disclosed on thursday their 
experiment may have been skewed by inaccuracies in a key piece of 
equipment that measured an emission of neutrons a sure sign of 
fusion the researchers said their probe may give false readings 
caused by heat at low temperatures 
its not as sure a thing as it was senior researcher james 
mahaffey said in atlanta it seemed like a sure thing now im 
getting nervous 
mahaffey said the experiment would be run again to determine if 
the equipment caused error in the projects results 
he acknowledged that mondays announcement of success might have 
been premature 
normally a nuclear fusion reaction requires extreme 
temperatures and pressures fusion at low temperatures socalled 
cold fusion could mean a cheap clean and nearly inexhaustible 
power source 
the georgia tech experiment and another announced monday by 
researchers at texas aampm appeared to confirm a march 23 reaction 
obtained by pons and fleischmann 
in eden and lius experiment a mass spectrometer detected a 
possible indicator of tritium a radioactive isotope of hydrogen 
commonly produced in fusion reactions 
the indicator was found when the experiment was run using 
deuterium a hydrogen isotope and component of deuterium oxide or 
heavy water eden said the indicator was not detected when the test 
was repeated with ordinary water 
both researchers cautioned that the results were preliminary and 
needed review by other scientists they also said they had not 
ruled out other explanations for what they observed 
we knew we had seen something that was exciting eden said 
it is open to alternative interpretation there is no question 
about that 
eden he and liu put together the experiment with existing lab 
equipment metals in stock and some heavy water sitting around 
the lab 
he said their major outofpocket expense was for about three 
pizzas bought by liu 
