<TEXT>
the state department responding to a call by 
a group of senators today registered its opposition to any effort 
to grant the palestine liberation organization membership status in 
the united nations 
in our view the selfdeclared palestinian state which we do 
not recognize does not meet the generally accepted international 
law criteria for statehood a department statement said it added 
that the plo does not qualify for membership in un agencies 
the 38 senators had urged secretary of state james a baker iii 
on thursday to oppose un recognition of the plo as a member 
state an upgrading of its current observer status 
any successful move by the un or related agencies to 
recognize the state of palestine would force us to seriously 
consider a range of punitive action including withholding us 
financial participation from those agencies the lawmakers said 
in a letter 
sen robert w kasten jr rwis and those who joined him said 
the plo was engaged in a public relations ploy to make 
headlines rather than confidencebuilding measures to make 
progress 
the senators said yasser arafats group should not be treated as 
a state because it does not control territory or any population and 
is not a government 
the state department responded today that the united states is 
ooposed to efforts to grant the plo rights and privileges exceeding 
its status as an observer organization within the un system 
the statement which was issued by the press office said the 
united states does not recognize the selfdeclared palestinian 
state 
to gain recognition as a member state the plo would have to 
apply to the security council where the united states is one of 
the five permanent members with veto power 
if the united states did not block the plos application 
twothirds of the 159 general assembly members would then have to 
vote for its admission as a member state 
baker testifying thursday before a senate appropriations 
subcommittee told kasten he had not seen the letter he said the 
united states would continue its talks with the plo despite 
statements by some plo elements that appeared to challenge israels 
right to exist 
baker also said the willingness of israeli prime minister 
yitzhak shamir to consider holding elections on the west bank and 
in gaza followed by negotiations on a permanent settlement was a 
new and hopeful idea that should be fully explored 
sen warren rudman rnh read several recent statements by 
plo officials that he said seemed to suggest they remain committed 
to the creation of a palestinian state and the destruction of 
israel 
statements such as those are clearly not helpful baker 
said we do look at statements such as that very carefully 
because we want to continue the dialogue with the plo under the 
conditions under which they were started 
but he said that the plo is composed of many dissident 
elements some of which are opposed to any dialogue with the united 
states and some which have not renounced terrorism 
to date we are satisfied that the plo is committed to what it 
has told us that it recognizes israels right to exist and that it 
has renounced terrorism in all of its forms baker said 
baker said shamirs proposal to hold elections among palestinian 
arabs on the west bank and in gaza was new different and 
significant 
he said the united states would encourage shamir egyptian 
president hosni mubarak and jordans king hussein who will be here 
for talks next week to preserve flexibility so that the options 
may be explored and if possible capitalized upon 
responding to questions baker said it would be difficult to 
conduct elections if the violence associated with the palestinian 
uprising in the occupied territories continues 
surely there has to be a greater degree of calm or tranquility 
before you get to elections he said 
bakers chief deputy meantime told a jewish audience the plo 
may be sincere in its declaration that it no longer seeks to 
destroy israel 
the evidence is mixed deputy secretary of state lawrence 
eagleburger told leaders of the united jewish appeal 
at the moment the jury is out he said when asked at a 
