urged newspaper editors to support public school improvement 
efforts saying such help is vital 
im really here to enlist your help cavazos told the 
american society of newspaper editors we must have your support 
in these endeavors if they are to be successful 
cavazos said high dropout rates low test scores drug abuse and 
a high degree of adult illiteracy mean the nation is beyond the 
at risk description in a 1983 report and already in trouble 
newspapers should urge more parental involvement in school 
management and educational decisions more teacher responsibility 
and more focus on early childhood education he said they should 
also insist on curricular reform and should promote university 
efforts to help primary and secondary schools he added 
cavazos also urged the editors to support some of the education 
priorities of the bush administration among them educational 
