with japan in february 465 billion up 317 percent from a 
threeyear low of 353 billion a month earlier 
the deficit with western europe was 624 million a 
deterioration from januarys rare 46 million surplus 
willard a workman director of international policy for the 
us chamber of commerce said the february report indicates that 
the drop in the deficit with japan in january was only a blip on 
the trade radar scope 
the stall in trade fits in with other evidence of slower growth 
in reports released friday including two consecutive flat months 
of industrial production in february and march a moderation in 
wholesale price inflation and the sharpest drop in business sales 
in february in more than two years 
