<TEXT>
a century after onetenth of the united 
states army converged on a parcel of land in indian territory to 
oversee the regions first great land run the blue coats are 
returning to fort reno 
about 500 reenactors including 150 military hobbyists from 
five states will take part in a weekend encampment organizers 
hope will authentically reproduce the excitement of the days before 
the run of 89 in which settlers stampeded the area to claim land 
that was free for the taking 
the goal is to give a good history lesson said deborah 
foreman who with her husband gary helped organize fort reno and 
indian territory days 
participants representing cavalry and infantry units of the 
