series of recommendations to the national institutes of health to 
help deal with the problem of fraud and misconduct in biomedical 
research 
paul j friedman a member of the medical panel told the 
conference that the group urged lessening of the competitive 
pressures that encourage abuses of good research and authorship 
practices 
