proposals to limit the number of publications reviewed for 
advancement instead of stressing productivity institutions would 
really concentrate on determining the quality of a small number of 
papers he said 
friedman associate dean of the school of medicine of the 
university of california at san diego said the panel recommended 
that by 1992 institutions receiving federal research funds be 
required to develop appropriate scientific and ethical 
standards 
