to romanticize the 60s were trying to provide an antidote to 
that 
their thesis is stern and unyielding the 60s was a time of 
naive idealism rooted in an inherent destructiveness 
collier and horowitz argue that the antiwar antiauthority 
prodrug culture of the 60s resulted in a breakdown of the system 
and the destruction of authority far from offering concrete 
remedies for society 60s leftists came up with jerrybuilt 
solutions that turned out to be disastrous 
