<TEXT>
bond prices rebounded sharply in heavy trading 
today following several government reports suggesting an easing of 
inflationary pressures 
the treasurys bellwether 30year issue jumped 1 316 point or 
about 12 for every 1000 in face amount as its yield which 
moves inversely to price fell to 903 percent from 915 percent 
late thursday 
the labor department reported that the producer price index of 
finished goods rose 04 percent in march better than the 05 
percent many had expected the index which measures inflation at 
the wholesale level had increased 1 percent in each of the two 
previous months 
the worst fears that some market observers had expressed 
regarding the possibility of a big increase in the producer price 
index were soundly refuted said marshall b front economist at 
the chicago investment and mutualfund management firm of stein roe 
amp farnham 
the government also said the us merchandise trade deficit for 
february widened by 209 percent to 105 billion from januarys 
898 billion 
and the government reported a 02 percent decline in the 
operating rate for us factories last month to 84 percent the 
second consecutive monthly decline business inventories rose 05 
percent in february while sales plunged 09 percent in their 
steepest decline in more than two years the government said 
the reports were consistent with expectations analysts said 
and fit in with other evidence of slower growth including 
lackluster retail sales and a slackening of employment growth in 
march 
other concerns about rising inflation and the possibility of 
the fed tightening seem to be less of a reality than before these 
figures were released front said 
inflation and high interest rates erode the value of 
fixedincome securities such as bonds 
in the secondary market for treasury bonds prices of shortterm 
notes were up between 1332 and 1732 point intermediate issues 
were point to 2732 point higher and longterm issues rose as 
much as 1 132 point according to telerate inc a financial 
reporting service 
the movement of a point equals a 10 change in the price of a 
bond with a 1000 face value 
the shearson lehman hutton daily treasury bond index which 
measures price movements on all outstanding treasury issues with 
maturities of a year or longer jumped 694 to 112523 
in corporate trading prices also advanced moodys investment 
grade corporate bond index which measures price movements on 80 
corporate bonds with maturities of five years or longer rose 088 
to 30002 
