889 while the discount fell 17 basis points to 859 percent 
yields on sixmonth bills declined to 916 percent as the discount 
also dropped 17 basis points to 867 percent yields on oneyear 
bills fell to 935 percent as the discount lost 19 basis points to 
863 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest on overnight loans between 
banks remained at 91316 percent the same as late thursday 
