proposal which is backed by holly farms management conagra 
shareholders were scheduled to vote on the proposal later in the 
day in omaha where that company is headquartered 
after the holly farms vote was taken officials adjourned the 
meeting until monday 
conagra has threatened court action if parts of a merger 
agreement reached with holly farms last november are not honored 
however tyson foods inc the rival poultry processor that has 
tried since last october to take over holly farms has vowed to 
continue its court fight to block the proposed merger with conagra 
tyson headquartered in springdale ark has made a cash offer 
of 6350 a share to holly farms stockholders for a deal worth 
about 115 billion buying holly farms would permit tyson to 
remain the largest poultry processor in the country 
the proposed conagraholly farms merger calls for a stock swap 
valued at 60 a share for holly farms stockholders holly farms 
shareholders would get 1875 shares of conagra stock for each share 
of holly farms stock traded 
a major point of argument in the conagraholly farms proposal is 
a provision allowing conagra to purchase major holly farms assets 
should the merger fall through 
tyson has filed suit in chancery court in delaware attacking the 
provision as an unfair attempt to block a buyout by anyone else 
the judge handling the suit has said the socalled assetoption 
agreement appears to be unenforcable and has issued a temporary 
injunction blocking it 
under the agreement conagra would be allowed to buy holly farms 
subsidiary harkers inc of lemars iowa for 1488 million holly 
farms of texas inc for a like amount and holly farms facilities in 
wilkesboro nc for 1275 million 
those purchases would cover some 34 percent of holly farms 
total assets 
