making allegedly fraudulent stock transactions in fact he doesnt 
even have a license to trade securities but he allegedly 
participated in the racketeering enterprise in other ways 
in one count lowell is alleged to have joined a march 1986 
telephone call regarding a 53 million payment with ivan boesky 
who provided much of the information leading to the milken 
indictment as part of a plea deal to settle fraudulent dealings 
and then lied to accountants to cover it up 
lowell also is named along with michael in the securities and 
exchange commissions civil suit charging them with insider trading 
and securities fraud 
