the stock and bond markets rallied impressively after the 
government released economic data suggesting that inflationary 
pressures are subsiding and the economy is taking a breather from 
the brisk pace of the last few years 
on wall street the stock market turned in its best showing in 
nearly five months the dow jones industrial average jumped 4106 
points friday to 233706 for its best singleday gain since it 
rose 4392 points last oct 20 
in the credit markets bonds scored their biggest gains since 
early december the treasurys bellwether 30year issue jumped 
1250 for every 1000 in face amount as its yield dropped to 
903 percent from 915 percent late thursday shortterm interest 
rates were also sharply lower 
the government reported friday that wholesale prices climbed 
more slowly in march than in the previous two months while the 
operating rate at the nations factories slowed business 
inventories rose and sales plunged 
at the same time the government said the nations trade deficit 
widened in to 105 billion in february from a rtevised 898 
billion in january 
the reports were either better or consistent with expectations 
what we have here is what federal reserve board chairman 
alan greenspan and the fed have been working for an economic 
pause that refreshes as opposed to a severe slowdown or 
recession said thomas f carpenter economist with asb capital 
management in washington 
the labor department reported that the producer price index of 
finished goods rose 04 percent in march the index which measures 
inflation at the wholesale level had increased 1 percent in each 
of the two previous months 
also in march the nations factories operated at an 84 percent 
rate 02 percent slower than in february and the second 
consecutive monthly decline according to the federal reserve board 
the commerce department said business inventories rose 05 
percent in february while sales plunged 09 percent in their 
steepest decline in more than two years 
with the exception of the trade figure analysts said the 
reports pointed to a slowdown in the growth of economic activity 
and fit in with other evidence that the economy is easing off the 
vigorous pace of recent years including lackluster retail sales 
and a slackening of employment growth in march 
we expect a slowdown in the economy and possibly a resurgence 
in growth later this year at that point people will be concerned 
about the economy again but now with the economy slowdown being 
confirmed with retail sales and other numbers the pendulum is 
beginning to swing back to a more balanced view and less 
