automobile sector the slowdown could be temporary as dealers add 
incentives during the second quarter to help boost sales he said 
but fridays data could fuel a reversal in interest rates 
predicted peter greenbaum bond market analyst with smith barney 
harris upham amp co how much lower depends on what happens with 
the dollar greenbaum said he expects the yield on the 
governments longterm bond to decline to 875 percent by the end 
